cs.SI, cs.IR, cs.CY, cs.SOC, cs.DL 

This paper deals with the analysis of web archiving services and their use on social media. It involves crawling and studying a large number of URLs from archive.is and Wayback Machine that were shared on social networks like Reddit, Twitter, Gab, and 4chan's Politically Incorrect board. The paper focuses on understanding the actors involved in this ecosystem, the content that gets archived, and how it is shared. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) and cs.IR (Information Retrieval), followed by cs.CY (Computers and Society), cs.SOC (Social and Behavioral Sciences), and cs.DL (Digital Libraries).
